Manchester United manager, Ole Gunnar Solskjaer, has rewarded Dylan Levitt for his debut, with a place in the squad for the Premier League fixture with Aston Villa, the Manchester Evening News reports. Levitt, 19, started against Astana in the Europa League on Thursday and is in contention to make a first domestic United matchday squad. Scott McTominay (ankle) was not among the United squad members, who reported at The Lowry Hotel on Saturday evening. Neither was Paul Pogba, who is expected to recover from his own ankle injury, in time for the visit of Tottenham on Wednesday. United have three left-backs to choose from, with Luke Shaw fit again to compete with Ashley Young and Brandon Williams. Confirmed United squad members: David de Gea, Lee Grant, Aaron Wan-Bissaka, Victor Lindelof, Axel Tuanzebe, Harry Maguire, Ashley Young, Brandon Williams, Luke Shaw, Andreas Pereira, Fred, Dylan Levitt, James Garner, Jesse Lingard, Juan Mata, Daniel James, Mason Greenwood, Marcus Rashford, Anthony Martial Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.